<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Remarks.</emphasis>
An adequate description of this species was given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ghauri" box="[940,1101,151,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" refString="Ghauri, M. S. K. (1971) Revision of the genus Nephotettix Matsumura (Homoptera, Cicadelloidea, Euscelidae) based on the type material. Bulletin of Entomological Research, 60 (3), 481 - 512. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 0007485300040438" type="journal article" year="1971">
Ghauri (
<number box="[1035,1093,152,176]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="1971.0">1971</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but some variation occurs as follows. Crown always with submarginal black transverse band but black markings of forewing vary (Plate IV: A– B, D–F). Although closely resembling 
<taxonomicName box="[633,801,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nephotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigropictus">
<emphasis box="[633,801,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">N. nigropictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general coloration, males of 
<taxonomicName box="[1211,1330,225,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nephotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvus">
<emphasis box="[1211,1330,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">N. parvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished by the distinctive aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[623,712,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1724,1746]" captionTargetBox="[218,1370,203,1694]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[212,1376,193,1702]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Nephotettix parvus Ishihara &amp; Kawase. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve, ventral view; C: subgenital plate, ventral view; D – E: style, dorsal view; F: connective, dorsal view; G &amp; H: aedeagus, ventral and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226702/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
Figs. 
<number box="[686,712,260,285]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
G–H) and females by the almost pointed crown (Plate IV: D–F).
</paragraph>
